programme.title: Panorama
programme.desc: Panorama goes undercover to reveal online doctor sites putting profit before patient care. In 2017 the Care Quality Commission issued a warning about the risks of buying drugs prescribed by doctors online. The programme discovers opiate-based painkillers and slimming tablets being sold to potentially vulnerable people and antibiotics being delivered across Europe in the face of warnings about resistance. Dr Faye Kirkland, journalist and GP, meets the families of patients who have died after online consultations and exposes the sites running rings around the regulators

programme.title: European Championships 2018
programme.desc: Live coverage of day six of the inaugural staging of the multi-sports event from Glasgow and Berlin, featuring swimming, diving, synchronised swimming, athletics, track cycling and mountain bike cycling. The athletics competition begins in earnest today with day one of events at Olympiastadion Berlin, which includes the commencement of the decathlon, and heats in the women's 400m hurdles and men's 400m. Elsewhere this morning, the heats of six swimming disciplines are scheduled to begin, the duet and mixed duet free synchronised swimming finals take place, the women's mountain bike cycling final is scheduled, and the track cycling continues with the women's keirin and Madison and men's keirin events at Sir Chris Hoy Velodrome. In addition to this, the men's mountain bike cycling final will see another champion crowned at Cathkin Braes Mountain Bike Trails this afternoon, and medals will also be decided in the women's 10m synchronised and men's 1m springboard diving disciplines. The synchronised swimming event comes to a conclusion with the gala event, while Tollcross International Swimming Centre plays host to six more swimming finals this evening, including the men's 50m butterfly, and the women's 1500m freestyle. Meanwhile, the first evening session of the athletics event takes place, and will feature the finals of the men's hammer, shot put and 10,000m. The decathlon event is set to continue with the running of the 400m, but the main attraction at Olympiastadion Berlin will undoubtedly be the running of the women's and men's 100m finals. Presented by Darragh Maloney and Peter Collins, with analysis from Andrew Bree, Derval O'Rourke, Earl McCarthy, Grainne Murphy, Jerry Kiernan, Martyn Irvine, and Sonia O'Sullivan, and reports by Darren Frehill, Des Curran, Evanne?Ni Chuilinn, Hugh Cahill, and Marie Crowe(c)

programme.desc: Live coverage of day seven of the inaugural staging of the multi-sports event from Glasgow and Berlin, featuring swimming, diving, cycling, golf and athletics. The women's road cycling time trial gold medallist is set to be decided on the streets of Glasgow city centre this morning, while the women's and men's 5km open water swimming finals are scheduled for Loch Lomond. Later in the evening, the swimming festivities get under way at Tollcross International Swimming Centre with six more gold medals set to be awarded, with events including the men's 200m breaststroke and women's 200m individual medley. Over in Germany, the second evening of the athletics competition at Olympiastadion Berlin will feature the men's long jump, shot put and discus finals, as well as that of the women's 10,000m, while the decathlon finally comes to a conclusion with the running of the 1500m. Geostorm
programme.desc: Two scientists race to avert a catastrophe when a series of climate-control satellites begin to malfunction. During their mission, they discover a conspiracy involving the satellites, which were designed to prevent natural disasters on Earth

programme.title: Split
programme.desc: Three teenagers are kidnapped and imprisoned by a man with multiple-personality disorder, and must plot their escape without ever knowing which of his 23 personas—young or old, male or female, benign or monstrous—they will confront on the way out

programme.title: The Jackal
programme.desc: Bruce Willis is the eponymous assassin hired by a Russian Mafia boss to kill the head of the FBI in revenge for his brother's death. Sidney Poitier, deputy Fbi chief, gets wind of the plot but nobody knows what The Jackal looks like or when or where he plans to strike - only ex-IRA terrorist Richard Gere can help but can he be trusted? Michael Caton-Jones' thriller racks up the tension as it follows the parallel paths of the hunter and the assassin with the clock ticking down in this re-make of The Day of the Jackal

programme.title: The Jackal
programme.desc: Bruce Willis is the eponymous assassin hired by a Russian Mafia boss to kill the head of the FBI in revenge for his brother's death. Sidney Poitier, deputy Fbi chief, gets wind of the plot but nobody knows what The Jackal looks like or when or where he plans to strike - only ex-IRA terrorist Richard Gere can help but can he be trusted? Michael Caton-Jones' thriller racks up the tension as it follows the parallel paths of the hunter and the assassin with the clock ticking down in this re-make of The Day of the Jackal

programme.title: Swimming With Sharks
programme.desc: A recent film-school grad gets a dream job as a personal assistant to a Hollywood mogul, who not only tyrannizes him, but also takes credit for his script

programme.title: Collateral
programme.desc: A character study-turned-thriller about a cabdriver who ferries a hit man on a late-night killing spree in Los Angeles. Foxx was nominated for Best Supporting Actor

programme.title: Dangerous Minds
programme.desc: An ex-marine is recruited to teach an inner-city class full of toughs. Based on actual events

programme.title: Wilson
programme.desc: A salty curmudgeon who is discontentment with how his life has stalled is shocked to discover he has a now-teenage daughter put up for adoption by his ex-wife after their split. He tries to reunite the family, but his abrasive personality makes getting reacquainted unpleasant for everyone

programme.title: Fried Green Tomatoes
programme.desc: Kathy Bates and Jessica Tandy head a fine cast in this story of female friendships in the South. Contains footage not shown in theaters. Idgie: Mary Stuart Masterson. Ruth: Mary-Louise Parker. Sipsey: Cicely Tyson. George: Stan Shaw. Frank: Nick Searcy. Ed: Gailard Sartain. Grady: Gary Basaraba. Buddy: Chris O'Donnell. Directed by Jon Avnet from a screenplay by Fannie Flagg and Carol Sobieski

programme.title: Maverick
programme.desc: Bret Maverick is a professional con man who needs money to participate in a poker tournament. To get it, he will have to face an endless line of bandits and problems, including Annabelle Bransford, a beautiful thieve that will stand in his way. Based on the television series Maverick created by Roy Huggins

programme.title: The Layover
programme.desc: Two girlfriends go on vacation to get away from their problems. But when a hurricane warning results in a long layover in St. Louis, they end up competing for the attention of a hunky fellow passenger

programme.title: The Hangover
programme.desc: The guests are set to arrive. The bride is getting ready. But the best man has lost the groom! When three friends get together for one last weekend-long bachelor party in Vegas, they think they had a good time. But it's very hard to remember, and they are suffering the dreadful after-effects of girls, party and alcohol. And then they realize they have somehow lost the groom! Now, they must struggle to retrace their wild weekend to find their friend and deliver the bridegroom to his wedding -- even as they suffer from one killer Hangover!

programme.title: Bad Company
programme.desc: When CIA agents Oakes and Pope try to secure a suitcase-sized nuke from a black-market dealer, they are ambushed and Pope is killed. Desperate for the bad guys to believe that Pope is still alive, Oakes recruits Pope's long-lost twin, a petty criminal

programme.title: The Wicker Man
programme.desc: Remake of the cult British thriller. A police sergeant visits a remote island off the Washington coast to search for a missing girl, but begins to fear for her safety when he finds the local community in thrall to paganism and mysterious beliefs. The sergeant's unease grows when the islanders deny the girl's existence and attempt to obstruct his investigation

programme.title: Man on Fire
programme.desc: Bloody revenge saga about a disgraced intelligence agent-turned-bodyguard who becomes a one-man army when the girl he's protecting is kidnapped

programme.title: A Perfect Getaway
programme.desc: An idyllic Hawaiian vacation turns into a nightmare when Cydney and Cliff (Milla Jovovich and Steve Zahn) discover their lives are in danger from a psychotic killer who is hunting visitors to the island. Timothy Olyphant, Chris Hemsworth, Kiele Sanchez. Directed by David Twohy

programme.title: Extreme Measures
programme.desc: A brilliant emergency-room physician (Hugh Grant) stumbles across a doctor's diabolical experiment involving humans. Gene Hackman. Jodie: Sarah Jessica Parker. Hare: David Morse. Directed by Michael Apted

programme.title: Extreme Measures
programme.desc: A brilliant emergency-room physician (Hugh Grant) stumbles across a doctor's diabolical experiment involving humans. Gene Hackman. Jodie: Sarah Jessica Parker. Hare: David Morse. Directed by Michael Apted

programme.title: Empire
programme.desc: Gangster thriller following a New York drug dealer who hopes to make a legal fortune on Wall Street. When a stockbroker offers him a business proposal, he thinks this will be his chance to go out on top, but soon finds out that he has been double-crossed and his last option is to get revenge

programme.title: Invincible
programme.desc: The story of the misfit outsider who rises through the ranks of a professional sport to enjoy inexplicable success has been stamped into celluloid more times than most folks can remember. INVINCIBLE tells the tale of bartender Vince Papale, a down-on-his-luck former teacher who decides to answer an open tryout for the Philadelphia Eagles. It doesn't take a genius to work out what happens next, but the twist here is that Vince Papale is a real person..

programme.title: The Bourne Identity
programme.desc: A blockbuster hit, The Bourne Identity stars Academy Award®-winner Matt Damon as a man fished out of the ocean by an Italian boat who has a complete loss of memory. Why are assassins after him? Why is he a master of martial arts and fluent in several languages? The answers will thrill and astonish you! Featuring amazing action scenes, taut direction, and beautiful European locations, The Bourne Identity is the opening introduction to a hugely popular action espionage franchise. Starring Matt Damon, Chris Cooper, Franka Potente, Julia Stiles

programme.title: Born on the Fourth of July
programme.desc: Oliver Stone's docudrama about paralyzed Vietnam vet Ron Kovic, who tries to reconcile memories of his idealistic youth with his post-war disillusionment

programme.title: Kingdom of Heaven
programme.desc: (2005) Ridley Scott's epic historical drama is set in the 12th century at the Crusader defence of Jerusalem. Orlando Bloom plays Balian de Ibelin, a village blacksmith and the illegitimate son of Godfrey de Ibelin (Liam Neeson), a crusader knight returned from the Holy Land. He persuades Balian that riches await those who go to defend the city and its Christian King Baldwin (Edward Norton) against the attack of Saladin (Ghassan Massoud), who seeks to win the city back for the Muslim faith. Balian, as well as falling for Baldwin's sister Sibylla (Eva Green), finds himself a power broker between the two factions, with the fate of the city in his hands. In English, and Arabic, Latin and Italian with English subtitles. M,W,R,S,,HD

programme.title: Mickey Blue Eyes
programme.desc: A British expat working in Manhattan as an auctioneer falls in love with a mobster's daughter. When he tries to ingratiate himself with her family, he ends up involved in criminal activity and is forced to pose as a wiseguy from Kansas City

programme.title: My Big Fat Greek Wedding
programme.desc: The proud Portokalos clan reels from the news that thirtysomething daughter (Nia Vardalos) has fallen for a teacher (John Corbett) who is not Greek. The rare romantic comedy that's actually both romantic and funny. Vardalos earned an Oscar nomination for her screenplay, which is adapted from her one-woman stage show. Michael Constantine and Lainie Kazan are excellent as the bride's parents. Directed by Joel Zwick; Rita Wilson and Tom Hanks are among the producers

programme.title: He's Just Not That Into You
programme.desc: An adaptation of a best-selling self-help book, 'He's Just Not That Into You' follows the story of a group who tries to sort out the signals that the sexes exchange. Gigi (Ginnifer Goodwin) imagines every man she meets is Mr. Right. She gets advice from a bar owner (Justin Long) who prides himself on understanding the ins and outs of the dating scene. Her friend Janine (Jennifer Connelly) seems to have a solid marriage with Ben (Bradley Cooper). Until he meets the attractive Anna (Scarlett Johansson), who's indifferent to Conor's (Kevin Connolly) pursuits. Another friend of Gigi's, Beth (Jennifer Aniston), enjoys a successful seven-year relationship with Neil (Ben Affleck), but dumps him when she realizes that he has no interest in getting married. Lastly, Mary (Drew Barrymore) is an advertising professional who tries to find love online. Will they finally figure out who is and who isn't into them?

programme.title: The American President
programme.desc: Andrew Shepherd is approaching the end of his first term as President of the United States. He's a widower with a young daughter and has proved to be popular with the public. His election seems assured. That is until he meets Sydney Ellen Wade, a paid political activist working for an environmental lobby group. He's immediately smitten with her and after several amusing attempts, they finally manage to go on a date (which happens to be a State dinner for the visiting President of France). His relationship with Wade opens the door for his prime political opponent, Senator Bob Rumson, to launch an attack on the President's character, something he could not do in the previous election as Shepherd's wife had only recently died

programme.title: Grosse Pointe Blank
programme.desc: A successful hit man re-evaluates his profession while attending his high-school reunion

programme.title: Chaos
programme.desc: A criminal mastermind (Wesley Snipes) pulls a bank heist that turns into a hostage situation and demands to negotiate with a recently suspended police detective (Jason Statham) in this twist-filled caper. Ryan Phillippe, Henry Czerny, Justine Waddell. Written and directed by Tony Giglio

programme.title: Taken
programme.desc: Liam Neeson stars as former CIA operative Bryan Mills, who's desperate to track down his kidnapped daughter in Pierre Morel's Luc Besson-produced action-thriller. Mills' life hasn't panned out well; his dedication to the CIA wrecked his marriage and made him neglect his daughter Kim. Now, retired from the Agency, he wants to make things up to Kim. But to do so, he has to contend with his ex-wife's animosity and Kim's new step-father's wealth. So when he has an opportunity to advance Kim's pop star ambitions he jumps at the chance, even if that means her and a friend crossing the Atlantic to brave 'the dangers of Europe'. As things turn out, he has a point: in Paris, the two girls are kidnapped by vicious Eastern European sex traffickers. As they are being abducted, Bryan tells one of the baddies, via Kim's mobile phone: 'I will look for you, I will find you, and I will kill you'. He subsequently does his best to make good on his promise, using all the violent tricks of the trade his time at the CIA taught him

programme.title: Taken

programme.title: Public Enemies
programme.desc: sonDirector Michael Mann's historical crime drama follows the efforts of top FBI agent Melvin Purvis (Christian Bale) in capturing notorious bank robber John Dillinger (Johnny Depp). A folk hero to the American public, Dillinger was virtually unstoppable at the height of his criminal career. J. Edgar Hoover's FBI was just being formed, and in order to turn his fledgling agency into a national police force, Hoover recruits Purvis to catch the most-elusive criminal in the country

programme.title: Kinsey
programme.desc: Provocative, intelligent biopic starring Liam Neeson as pioneering sex researcher Alfred Kinsey and Laura Linney as his freethinking wife. Chris O'Donnell, Peter Sarsgaard, Timothy Hutton, John Lithgow, Tim Curry. Directed by Bill Condon

programme.title: Rules Don't Apply
programme.desc: In 1958 Hollywood, a romance blossoms between a pious actress and a right-wing chauffeur—even though both of them work for reclusive billionaire Howard Hughes, who forbids his employees to date each other. Their secret liaison plays out while Hughes' aviation innovations keep pace with his debilitating eccentricities

programme.title: Selena
programme.desc: Biopic of the Tejano singer who was gunned down by an assistant at the height of her fame. The focus is primarily on Selena's relationship with her family, including her demanding manager-father, and her rise to stardom

programme.title: The Birth of a Nation
programme.desc: This historical drama recounts a real-life slave revolt that occurred in 1831 Virginia, led by a black preacher named Nat Turner. Turner is so appalled by the horrors he sees while sermonizing that he is moved to fight back

programme.title: Elizabeth
programme.desc: Cate Blanchett reprises her role as Queen Elizabeth I in this account of her efforts to defend England from King Philip II of Spain, while trying to suppress her attraction to the dashing Sir Walter Raleigh

programme.title: Jackie
programme.desc: In the immediate aftermath of the assassination of President John F. Kennedy, his wife Jacqueline deals with her immense grief while caring for her young family and making plans for his funeral procession. At the same time, a bereaved nation watches on

programme.title: The Zookeeper's Wife
programme.desc: A husband and wife in Nazi-occupied Poland use their position as caretakers at the Warsaw Zoo to shepherd Jews out of the country. Based on the non-fiction book by Diane Ackerman ("A Natural History of the Senses")

programme.title: Conan the Barbarian
programme.desc: John Milius's sword-and-sorcery fantasy is based on the works of Robert E Howard, king of the pulp fiction explosion of the inter-War years. The orphaned and enslaved Conan grows to become Arnold Schwarzenegger, vowing vengeance on Thulas Doom (James Earl Jones), the slayer of his family. En route, he picks up the requisite strange companions before confronting Doom and, in the process, saving the captured princess (Valerie Quennessen) whose father is suitably grateful. Possibly not the most cerebral of films but rollicking good stuff all the same

programme.title: The Book of Eli

But things go disastrously wrong and all but one of the team are massacred. As the sole survivor, Hunt must now try to prove his innocence and discover the real betrayer before he is terminated by his own government. And thus begins a top-class, high-octane chase thriller, packed with jaw-dropping special effects and stunts

It all begins when Frodo receives a ring from his uncle Bilbo (Ian Holm) and wizard Gandalf (Ian McKellen) discovers it is the Unique Ring itself. This powerful ring has been conceived by Sauron, the dark Lord of Mordor (Sala Baker), and with it, it is possible to enslave the whole of the Middle-earth through the use of dark forces. To destroy the ring, Frodo must take it to a distant mountain in Mordor, a region controlled by the Master of Evil. Fortunately, he is accompanied by a group formed by Hobbits Sam (Sean Astin), Merry (Dominic Monaghan) and Pippin (Billy Boyd), as well as Gandalf, the human warriors Aragorn (Viggo Mortensen) and Boromir (Sean Bean), and elf Legolas (Orlando Bloom). programme.title: Independence Day
programme.desc: Roland Emmerich's blockbuster of a science fiction film sees aliens reach Earth. And they're decidedly hostile - their plan is to suck the planet of all its resources and leave behind a burnt cinder circling the sun before moving on. Planting giant ships above the world's major cities, they unleash destruction on an unprecedented scale (superbly caught by the special effects). All attempts at fighting back are met by hordes of fighter craft until pilot Steven Hiller manages to down one and capture the pilot. In tandem, scientist David Levinson, having worked out their purpose, also works out a way to destroy them but he and Hiller need a space craft. Which brings them to a secret base near Las Vegas. The child of countless science fiction movies, Independence Day is rollicking, fast-moving fun and if the fate of the remains of the human race is never in doubt, there's enough tension and action to carry even the most jaundiced viewer along

programme.desc: Academy Award winner George Clooney stars in the title role of this suspense thriller, filmed on location in Italy. Alone among assassins, Jack (played by Mr. Clooney) is a master craftsman. When a job in Sweden ends more harshly than expected for this American abroad, he vows to his contact Larry (Bruce Altman) that his next assignment will be his last. Jack reports to the Italian countryside, where he holes up in a small town and relishes being away from death for a spell. The assignment, as specified by a Belgian woman, Mathilde (Thekla Reuten of 'In Bruges'), is in the offing as a weapon is constructed. Surprising himself, Jack seeks out the friendship of local priest Father Benedetto (Italian stage and screen veteran Paolo Bonacelli) and pursues romance with local woman Clara (Italian leading lady Violante Placido). programme.title: Behind Enemy Lines
programme.desc: Loosely based on a true story, John Moore's all-action thriller stars Owen Wilson as US Navy helicopter pilot Lt Chris Burnett, who's part of the NATO force observing the peace treaty during the conflict in former Yugoslavia. Bored with routine duties, he flies off his designated route and spots Serb forces breaching the peace agreement, but they spot him too and down his craft. Behind enemy lines and with the Serbs on his trail, determined to stop him getting to safety with his story, his only hope is that his commander Admiral Reigart sends in a rescue mission. But NATO refuse; acknowledging Burnett's very existence could end the fragile ceasefire, so he's on his own..

William, lacking a proper pedigree, convinces Chaucer to forge genealogy documents that will pass him off as a knight. programme.title: Cloudy With a Chance of Meatballs
programme.desc: When Flint Lockwood's latest contraption accidentally destroys the town square and rockets up into the clouds, he thinks his inventing career is over. Then something amazing happens as delicious cheeseburgers start raining from the sky. His machine actually works! But when people greedily ask for more and more food, the machine starts to run amok, unleashing spaghetti tornadoes and giant meatballs that threaten the world. Now it's up to Flint, with the help of weather girl Sam Sparks and Steve, his talking monkey assistant, to find some way to shut down the machine before the world is covered in super-sized meatballs

programme.title: The Mexican
programme.desc: Academy award nominated megastar Brad Pitt stars alongside Academy Award winning beauty Julia Roberts in this fun-filled romantic comedy packed with adventure. A clumsy criminal is put in a position where he not only has to save his own skin, but that of his girlfriend in this comedy with strong undercurrents of romance. Jerry Welbach (Pitt) is a low-level Mafia "mechanic" whose ineptitude is countered by frequent (but unpredictable) bursts of dumb luck. Jerry's girlfriend Samantha (Roberts) wants him to get out of the business, and after his latest blunder lands capo Arnold Margolese (Gene Hackman) in jail, so does mid-level crime kingpin Bernie Nayman (Bob Balaban). But Bernie insists that Jerry do one last errand for the mob before they let him find employment elsewhere -- he has to go to Mexico and recover a rare and very valuable pistol, which is said to be cursed. While Samantha objects to Jerry taking the assignment, he isn't in much of a position to argue; Jerry heads south of the border, while Samantha, in a huff, sets out for Las Vegas. Once in Mexico, Jerry finds the pistol easily enough, but making his way back to the States proves to be an unexpected challenge

programme.title: Dodgeball
programme.desc: (2004) Peter La Fleur (VInce Vaughn) owns Average Joe's Gym, a scruffy establishment with a loyal clientele, while across the street Globo Gym, owned by White Goodman (Ben Stiller), is all glass and chrome and full of toned muscle. When La Fleur learns that he must pay the bank $50,000 in 30 days, Goodman is overjoyed: he can acquire his rival's building, knock it down and have the car park his gym's always needed. But La Fleur decides to set up a money-earning dodgeball tournament (a sport that consists of not being hit by balls hurled by the opposing team). And, of course, La Fleur's team of misfits end up in a face-off against Goodman's tough pros in the final. Rawson Marshall Thurber's debut feature is a mix of verbal and physical humour, and, if the outcome is never in doubt, both Vaughn and Stiller throw themselves into the venture with enjoyable gusto. M,W,R,S,,HD
